ctdlswVersion.name: ctdlswVersion
ctdlswVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of the DLSw firmware in textual format.

ctdlswAdminStatus.name: ctdlswAdminStatus
ctdlswAdminStatus.description: Sets the system-wide administrative state of DLSw services.

ctdlswOperStatus.name: ctdlswOperStatus
ctdlswOperStatus.description: Indicates the current system-wide status of DLSw services.

ctdlswUpTime.name: ctdlswUpTime
ctdlswUpTime.description: Indicates the time (in hundredths of a second) since the DLSw services portion of the system was enabled.

ctdlswOperVirtualRingNumber.name: ctdlswOperVirtualRingNumber
ctdlswOperVirtualRingNumber.description: Specifies the operational ring/segment number that uniquely identifies the virtual segment to which this DLSw is connected. This object may only be modified when ctdlswOperStatus is disabled.

ctdlswNBLocalFilterType.name: ctdlswNBLocalFilterType
ctdlswNBLocalFilterType.description: Specifies the type of filtering to be applied to NetBIOS frames received on a local LAN segment. If set to block(1), any frame matching any entry in ctdlswNBLocalFilterTable will not be forwarded. If set to pass(2), only frames matching any entry in ctdlswNBLocalFilterTable will be forwarded.

ctdlswNBRemoteFilterType.name: ctdlswNBRemoteFilterType
ctdlswNBRemoteFilterType.description: Specifies the type of filtering to be applied to NetBIOS frames received from a remote DLSw partner. If set to block(1), any frame matching any entry in ctdlswNBRemoteFilterTable will not be forwarded. If set to pass(2), only frames matching any entry in ctdlswNBRemoteFilterTable will be forwarded.

ctdlswMacLocalFilterType.name: ctdlswMacLocalFilterType
ctdlswMacLocalFilterType.description: Specifies the type of address filtering to be applied to SNA MAC frames received on a local LAN segment. If set to block(1), any frame matching any entry in ctdlswMacLocalFilterTable will not be forwarded. If set to pass(2), only frames matching any entry in ctdlswMacLocalFilterTable will be forwarded.

ctdlswMacRemoteFilterType.name: ctdlswMacRemoteFilterType
ctdlswMacRemoteFilterType.description: Specifies the type of address filtering to be applied to SNA MAC frames received from a remote DLSw partner. If set to block(1), any frame matching any entry in ctdlswMacRemoteFilterTable will not be forwarded. If set to pass(2), only frames matching any entry in ctdlswMacRemoteFilterTable will be forwarded.

ctdlswAcceptDynamicTConn.name: ctdlswAcceptDynamicTConn
ctdlswAcceptDynamicTConn.description: Specifies whether this DLSw allows unconfigured DLSw partners to establish transport connections. Yes(1) means unconfigured DLSw partners may establish transport connections with this DLSw. No(2) means only user configured DLSw partners may establish transport connections with this DLSw.

ctdlswDefaultPortNumber.name: ctdlswDefaultPortNumber
ctdlswDefaultPortNumber.description: Specifies the index of the port whose associated IP address will be used to identify this DLSw node to its DLSw partners. The value must be consistent with 'ifIndex' of mib-II.

ctdlswPortTable.name: ctdlswPortTable
ctdlswPortTable.description: This table contains an entry for each port, and specifies configuration parameters used to establish circuits over that port. This table is indexed by ctdlswPortName, which identifies the port for which an entry exists. These port configuration entries will be provided automatically based on the physical port configuration. These entries cannot be created or deleted - only modified.

ctdlswPortEntry.name: ctdlswPortEntry
ctdlswPortEntry.description: Each entry specifies configuration parameters for a port for which the entry exists.

ctdlswPortIndex.name: ctdlswPortIndex
ctdlswPortIndex.description: Specifies a unique value for each port. Values are derived from 'ifIndex' of mib-II.

ctdlswPortName.name: ctdlswPortName
ctdlswPortName.description: Specifies the user friendly name for this port.

ctdlswPortAddress.name: ctdlswPortAddress
ctdlswPortAddress.description: Specifies the MAC address of this port.

ctdlswPortAdminStatus.name: ctdlswPortAdminStatus
ctdlswPortAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of DLSw frame forwarding for this port.

ctdlswPortOperStatus.name: ctdlswPortOperStatus
ctdlswPortOperStatus.description: Specifies the current operating status of DLSw frame forwarding for this port.

ctdlswPortUpTime.name: ctdlswPortUpTime
ctdlswPortUpTime.description: Indicates the time (in hundredths of a second) since this port was enabled. A value of zero means this port is not presently enabled.

ctdlswLocalNBFilterTable.name: ctdlswLocalNBFilterTable
ctdlswLocalNBFilterTable.description: A list of NETBIOS source-destination name pairs whose frames are allowed (or not allowed) to be forwarded via this DLSw. Only source-destination name pairs from locally generated NetBIOS frames are compared against entries in this table.

ctdlswLocalNBFilterEntry.name: ctdlswLocalNBFilterEntry
ctdlswLocalNBFilterEntry.description: Information for one NetBIOS source-destination name pair.

ctdlswLocalNBFilterSrcName.name: ctdlswLocalNBFilterSrcName
ctdlswLocalNBFilterSrcName.description: The source NETBIOS name to filter on.

ctdlswLocalNBFilterDestName.name: ctdlswLocalNBFilterDestName
ctdlswLocalNBFilterDestName.description: The destination NETBIOS NAME to filter on.

ctdlswLocalNBFilterControl.name: ctdlswLocalNBFilterControl
ctdlswLocalNBFilterControl.description: Set this object to delete(3) to remove this entry. Set to create(2) to add this entry. A get of this object will return other(1).

ctdlswRemoteNBFilterTable.name: ctdlswRemoteNBFilterTable
ctdlswRemoteNBFilterTable.description: A list of NETBIOS source-destination name pairs whose frames are allowed (or not allowed) to be forwarded via this DLSw. Only source-destination name pairs from NetBIOS frames received from remote DLSw partners are compared against entries in this table.

ctdlswRemoteNBFilterEntry.name: ctdlswRemoteNBFilterEntry
ctdlswRemoteNBFilterEntry.description: Information for one NetBIOS source-destination name pair.

ctdlswRemoteNBFilterSrcName.name: ctdlswRemoteNBFilterSrcName
ctdlswRemoteNBFilterSrcName.description: The source NETBIOS name to filter on.

ctdlswRemoteNBFilterDestName.name: ctdlswRemoteNBFilterDestName
ctdlswRemoteNBFilterDestName.description: The destination NETBIOS name to filter on.

ctdlswRemoteNBFilterControl.name: ctdlswRemoteNBFilterControl
ctdlswRemoteNBFilterControl.description: Set this object to delete(3) to remove this entry. Set to create(2) to add this entry. A get of this object will return other(1).

ctdlswLocalMacFilterTable.name: ctdlswLocalMacFilterTable
ctdlswLocalMacFilterTable.description: A list of source-destination MAC address pairs whose frames are allowed (or not allowed) to be forwarded via this DLSw. Only source-destination name pairs from locally generated SNA MAC frames are compared against entries in this table.

ctdlswLocalMacFilterEntry.name: ctdlswLocalMacFilterEntry
ctdlswLocalMacFilterEntry.description: Information for one source-destination MAC address pair.

ctdlswLocalMacFilterSrcAddr.name: ctdlswLocalMacFilterSrcAddr
ctdlswLocalMacFilterSrcAddr.description: The source MAC Address to filter on.

ctdlswLocalMacFilterSrcMask.name: ctdlswLocalMacFilterSrcMask
ctdlswLocalMacFilterSrcMask.description: The source MAC Address mask to filter on.

ctdlswLocalMacFilterDestAddr.name: ctdlswLocalMacFilterDestAddr
ctdlswLocalMacFilterDestAddr.description: The destination MAC Address to filter on.

ctdlswLocalMacFilterDestMask.name: ctdlswLocalMacFilterDestMask
ctdlswLocalMacFilterDestMask.description: The destination MAC Address mask to filter on.

ctdlswLocalMacFilterControl.name: ctdlswLocalMacFilterControl
ctdlswLocalMacFilterControl.description: Set this object to delete(3) to remove this entry. Set to create(2) to add this entry. A get of this object will return other(1).

ctdlswRemoteMacFilterTable.name: ctdlswRemoteMacFilterTable
ctdlswRemoteMacFilterTable.description: A list of source-destination MAC address pairs whose frames are allowed (or not allowed) to be forwarded via this DLSw. Only source-destination name pairs from SNA MAC frames received from remote DLSw partners are compared against entries in this table.

ctdlswRemoteMacFilterEntry.name: ctdlswRemoteMacFilterEntry
ctdlswRemoteMacFilterEntry.description: Information for one source-destination MAC address pair.

ctdlswRemoteMacFilterSrcAddr.name: ctdlswRemoteMacFilterSrcAddr
ctdlswRemoteMacFilterSrcAddr.description: The source MAC Address to filter on.

ctdlswRemoteMacFilterSrcMask.name: ctdlswRemoteMacFilterSrcMask
ctdlswRemoteMacFilterSrcMask.description: The source MAC Address mask to filter on.

ctdlswRemoteMacFilterDestAddr.name: ctdlswRemoteMacFilterDestAddr
ctdlswRemoteMacFilterDestAddr.description: The destination MAC Address to filter on.

ctdlswRemoteMacFilterDestMask.name: ctdlswRemoteMacFilterDestMask
ctdlswRemoteMacFilterDestMask.description: The destination MAC Address mask to filter on.

ctdlswRemoteMacFilterControl.name: ctdlswRemoteMacFilterControl
ctdlswRemoteMacFilterControl.description: Set this object to delete(3) to remove this entry. Set to create(2) to add this entry. A get of this object will return other(1).

ctdlswTConnTable.name: ctdlswTConnTable
ctdlswTConnTable.description: A list of transport connections which are either user defined or dynamically created for this DLSw.

ctdlswTConnRemoteTAddr.name: ctdlswTConnRemoteTAddr
ctdlswTConnRemoteTAddr.description: Specifies the remote transport address for this transport connection. It can be defined by the user, or established dynamically upon receiving a connection setup request from another DLSw.

ctdlswTConnControl.name: ctdlswTConnControl
ctdlswTConnControl.description: Set this object to delete(3) to remove this entry. Set to create(2) to add this entry. A get of this object will return other(1).

ctdlswTConnUpTime.name: ctdlswTConnUpTime
ctdlswTConnUpTime.description: Indicates the time (in hundredths of a second) since this transport connection was last established. A value of zero means this transport connection is not presently established.

ctdlswTConnOperStatus.name: ctdlswTConnOperStatus
ctdlswTConnOperStatus.description: Indicates the status of this transport connection.

ctdlswTConnType.name: ctdlswTConnType
ctdlswTConnType.description: Indicates the means by which this transport connection was determined. Configured(1) means this entry was user defined. Dynamic(2) means this entry was not user defined but was created as a result of a connection initiated by another DLSw.

ctdlswEventAdminStatus.name: ctdlswEventAdminStatus
ctdlswEventAdminStatus.description: Set the administrative state of Data Link Switching event logging. enabled(3) causes the event log to become active. disabled(2) causes the event log to become inactive.

ctdlswEventMaxEntries.name: ctdlswEventMaxEntries
ctdlswEventMaxEntries.description: Sets the maximum number of entries allowed in the event log table. When the number of entries reaches the value of ctdlswEventMaxEntries the first (oldest) entry is deleted to allow a new entry to be added.

ctdlswEventTraceAll.name: ctdlswEventTraceAll
ctdlswEventTraceAll.description: enabled(3) allows logging of all event types. disabled(2) causes the event log filter table to specify which events to log.

ctdlswEventFilterTable.name: ctdlswEventFilterTable
ctdlswEventFilterTable.description: This table contains descriptions of how to filter log entries.

ctdlswEventFilterEntry.name: ctdlswEventFilterEntry
ctdlswEventFilterEntry.description: Each entry specifies the filter for log entries. The instance ctdlswEventProtocol refers to the instance used in the nwRtgProtocolTable and nwComponentTable specified by the ctrouter-mib.txt.

ctdlswEventFltrProtocol.name: ctdlswEventFltrProtocol
ctdlswEventFltrProtocol.description: Selects the protocol to log events from.

ctdlswEventFltrIfNum.name: ctdlswEventFltrIfNum
ctdlswEventFltrIfNum.description: Specifies the port on which to log events.

ctdlswEventFltrControl.name: ctdlswEventFltrControl
ctdlswEventFltrControl.description: Setting this field to delete will allow entries to be removed from the table. This is done by adding new entries with instance fields that match the entry to be removed from the table. The new entry being added must have this control field set to delete in order for the matching entry already in the table to be deleted. Setting this field to add will add the entry to the table.

ctdlswEventFltrType.name: ctdlswEventFltrType
ctdlswEventFltrType.description: This bit field mask filter will allow only events of certain types to be logged. By default all types will be logged. Clearing event types from this field will cause those types not to be logged. Adding event types to this field will enable those types to be logged.

ctdlswEventFltrSeverity.name: ctdlswEventFltrSeverity
ctdlswEventFltrSeverity.description: This filter controls the amount of logging by ignoring events of lower priority than that specified by the filter value. Specifying highest(1) causes all events except those of highest severity to be ignored. Specifying highmed(2) causes lowest severity events to be ignored. Specifying highlow(3) causes all events to be logged. highmed(2) is the default setting.

ctdlswEventFltrAction.name: ctdlswEventFltrAction
ctdlswEventFltrAction.description: This field specifies how the events are to be logged. Specifying log(1) stores the events in the event log table (defined below). Specifying trap(2) sends events out through the trap mechanism. Specifying logTrap(3) does both.

ctdlswEventTable.name: ctdlswEventTable
ctdlswEventTable.description: This table contains all events that have been logged.

ctdlswEventEntry.name: ctdlswEventEntry
ctdlswEventEntry.description: Each entry specifies events that have been logged.

ctdlswEventTime.name: ctdlswEventTime
ctdlswEventTime.description: This number specifies when the event was logged.

ctdlswEventSeverity.name: ctdlswEventSeverity
ctdlswEventSeverity.description: Specifies the severity of the event logged.

ctdlswEventProtocol.name: ctdlswEventProtocol
ctdlswEventProtocol.description: Specifies the protocol where the event occured.

ctdlswEventIfNum.name: ctdlswEventIfNum
ctdlswEventIfNum.description: Specifies the port the event occurred on.

ctdlswEventTextString.name: ctdlswEventTextString
ctdlswEventTextString.description: Specifies the actual text string to be logged.
